                        West Bengal has a meagre 2000 beds in the state mental hospitals for over 1.25 crore of people with mental health conditions. There are approximately 450 psychiatrists catering to the needs of the population; roughly amounting to 1 psychiatrist for every 27,000 'patients'.

                    </p>
